// Regression: a `run <sys>` inside a proc in an IMPORTED module (a non-entry compilation unit) must
// resolve the system symbol across units. Under per-unit codegen the system body emits once in unit 0
// and this entry unit references the module proc, which itself references `@arche.bump` from its own
// (non-entry) unit — the cross-unit SYS declare path. Asserts the system actually mutated pool state, so
// it fails loudly if the declare ever regresses. Passes in BOTH whole-program and per-unit modes.
// RUN: %arche build -o %t %s && %t | grep -qF "n=1"
#import { "./run_helper_lib" }
main :: proc() {
  run_helper_lib.step()();
}
